title: sandbox
new-page: true
is-special: true
is-hand: true
go-to: sandbox_menu

= Sandbox Menu

@sandbox_menu

- @editresources: Edit Resources
- @editpara_resources: Edit Paramilitary Resources
- @editbudget: Edit Budget
- @editeconomy: Edit Economy
- @editrelations: Edit Party Relations
- @editpartysupport: Edit Party Support
- @editpartyfactions: Edit Party Factions
- @editironfront: Edit Arditi del Popolo
- @editparamilitary: Edit Paramilitary Groups
- @editreichswehr: Edit Army and Police
- @root: Exit Sandbox Menu

@editpartyfactions

- @editcommunist: Edit Communist Faction
- @editmaximalist: Edit Maximalist Faction
- @editlabour: Edit Labour Faction
- @editreformist: Edit Reformist Faction
- @editsyndicalist: Edit Syndicalist Faction
- @returnsandbox: Return To Sandbox

@editresources

- @add10resources: Add 10 Resources
- @add20resources: Add 20 Resources
- @add100resources: Add 100 Resources
- @subtract10resources: Subtract 10 Resources
- @subtract20resources: Subtract 20 Resources
- @subtract100resources: Subtract 100 Resources
- @returnsandbox: Return To Sandbox

@add10resources
go-to: sandbox_menu
on-arrival: {!
Q.resources += 10;
!}

Added 10 resources to the party's stockpile.

@add20resources
go-to: sandbox_menu
on-arrival: {!
Q.resources += 20;
!}

Added 20 resources to the party's stockpile.

@add100resources
go-to: sandbox_menu
on-arrival: {!
Q.resources += 100;
!}

Added 100 resources to the party's stockpile, stop being greedy.

@subtract10resources
go-to: sandbox_menu
on-arrival: {!
Q.resources -= 10;
!}

Removed 10 resources from the party's stockpile.

@subtract20resources
go-to: sandbox_menu
on-arrival: {!
Q.resources -= 20;
!}

Removed 20 resources from the party's stockpile.

@subtract100resources
go-to: sandbox_menu
on-arrival: {!
Q.resources -= 100;
!}

Removed 100 resources from the party's stockpile. This doesn't go to the homeless or anything, why would you do this?

